

Higher Order Functions
----------------------

Higher order are functions that either accept one or more functions as arguments or returns a functions.

(or)

Function which takes another function as an arguments is call Higher Order functions.


Call Back Function
==================

Function which get passed as an arguments to another function is called callback function.


Exmaple

const add = (a, b) => a + b;
const sub = (a, b) => a - b;

const calculator = (n1, n2, operator) => {
    return operator(n1, n2);
}

console.log(calculator(10, 5, add)); //15

console.log(calculator(10, 5, sub)); //5

